channel.title: Could not find process:Java
channel.description:
i get this error message"could not find process:java" when i run my runserver.bat
heres what the runserver says when i edit it in notepad
[code]@echo off cls echo Voule Auto restart tskill java /a echo Restarting server title EvolutionX RunServer java -Xmx512m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server cls[/code]
i have java jdk 20, can someone guide me how to get rid of the error

item.title: Could not find process:Java
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

@echo off cls echo Voule Auto restart [b]tskill java /a[/b] echo Restarting server title EvolutionX RunServer java -Xmx512m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server cls

Its not a problem at all. The command “tskill” is just an abbreviation for “Task Kill”. If it says it cannot find the process, it just means it is not currently running. I recommend getting rid of that line, as it will close all other java applets running on the Java process.
